#
# 1. Create Salesforce Connected App:
#    - Go to Setup > Apps > App Manager
#    - Create New Connected App
#    - Enable OAuth 2.0
#    - Configure callback URIs
#    - Set appropriate OAuth scopes
#    - Download consumer key and secret
#
# 2. Configure API Access:
#    - Enable API access for user profiles
#    - Configure field-level security
#    - Set up sharing rules
#    - Create custom fields if needed
#
# 3. Set Environment Variables:
#    - Copy this template to .env
#    - Fill in all required values
#    - Test API connectivity
#
# 4. Database Setup:
#    - Create PostgreSQL database
#    - Run database migrations
#    - Verify table creation
#
# 5. Test Integration:
#    - Run test_salesforce_enhanced.py
#    - Check API health endpoints
#    - Verify OAuth flow
#
# 6. Configure Advanced Features:
#    - Enable AI features if desired
#    - Set up webhooks for real-time updates
#    - Configure analytics and monitoring
#
# 7. Security Configuration:
#    - Set strong encryption keys
#    - Configure audit logging
#    - Enable compliance features
#
# 8. Production Deployment:
#    - Use HTTPS for all endpoints
#    - Configure load balancing
#    - Set up monitoring and alerting
#
# Environment-Specific Notes:
#
# Production:
# - Use login.salesforce.com for OAuth
# - Ensure HTTPS for all endpoints
# - Enable comprehensive logging
# - Configure backup and recovery
#
# Sandbox:
# - Use test.salesforce.com for OAuth
# - Use sandbox organization ID
# - Enable debug logging
# - Test all features before production
#
# Developer:
# - Use mock services for testing
# - Enable debug mode
# - Use test database
# - Disable production features
